arlic, sesame oil and soy sauce into mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer into bowl with chicken. Add lemongrass to bowl with chicken and stir to coat completely. Cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator to marinate for a minimum of 3 hours or overnight (see Tips). Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Drizzle chicken with a little of the vegetable oil and fry on both sides until browned and cooked through (approx. 5-10 minutes on each side). Cut into thin slices (approx. 5 mm). Cover and set aside to cool."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pickled carrot"},{"content":"Place vinegar, sugar and salt into mixing bowl and heat <b>5 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a bowl. Add carrot to bowl and stir to combine. Cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for a minimum of 30 minutes."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Chicken liver pâté"},{"content":"Place garlic and onion into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add butter and cook <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add all remaining pâté ingredients and cook <b>5-7 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>, until livers are cooked but still pink, then blend <b>30 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Place a fine-mesh sieve over a bowl and transfer pâté mixture into it. Using spatula, press pâté through sieve to get a smooth consistency. Discard contents of sieve. Transfer pâté into a sealable container and place into refrigerator until ready to use. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Drain and discard pickling liquid from carrots. Cut baguette into 4 portions, then slice each portion into halves lengthways. Spread each portion with mayonnaise and reserved pâté, then layer with cooled chicken, pickled chillies, cucumber, pickled carrot and coriander (optional) to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If you are short on time, you can marinate the chicken for only 1 hour, however the flavours won't be quite as strong.","You can cover pâté with extra melted butter to seal, if desired. You can store it in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.","To make your own baguette, please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook.<\/em>","To make your own mayonnaise, please refer to<em> The Basic Cookbook or Everyday Cookbook<\/em>."],"basicInfo":["easy","45m","4h 35m","4 portions"]}